# Excel Functions Cheat Sheet ðŸ“Š

A quick reference guide for useful Excel functions with syntax and examples.

---

## **1. Basic Math & Statistical Functions**
| Function | Syntax | Description |
|----------|--------|-------------|
| **SUM** | `=SUM(number1, [number2], ...)` | Adds all numbers in a range. |
| **AVERAGE** | `=AVERAGE(number1, [number2], ...)` | Calculates the average of numbers. |
| **COUNT** | `=COUNT(value1, [value2], ...)` | Counts cells with numbers. |
| **MAX** | `=MAX(number1, [number2], ...)` | Returns the largest value. |
| **MIN** | `=MIN(number1, [number2], ...)` | Returns the smallest value. |

---

## **2. Logical Functions**
| Function | Syntax | Description |
|----------|--------|-------------|
| **IF** | `=IF(logical_test, [value_if_true], [value_if_false])` | Conditional check. |
| **AND** | `=AND(logical1, [logical2], ...)` | Returns `TRUE` if all conditions are met. |
| **OR** | `=OR(logical1, [logical2], ...)` | Returns `TRUE` if any condition is met. |
| **IFS** | `=IFS(condition1, value1, condition2, value2, ...)` | Multiple IF conditions. |

---

## **3. Lookup & Reference Functions**
| Function | Syntax | Description |
|----------|--------|-------------|
| **VLOOKUP** | `=VLOOKUP(lookup_value, table_array, col_index_num, [range_lookup])` | Vertical lookup. |
| **HLOOKUP** | `=HLOOKUP(lookup_value, table_array, row_index_num, [range_lookup])` | Horizontal lookup. |
| **INDEX & MATCH** | `=INDEX(array, row_num, [column_num])` + `=MATCH(lookup_value, lookup_array, [match_type])` | Flexible lookup combo. |
| **XLOOKUP** | `=XLOOKUP(lookup_value, lookup_array, return_array, [if_not_found], [match_mode], [search_mode])` | Modern replacement for VLOOKUP. |

---

## **4. Text Functions**
| Function | Syntax | Description |
|----------|--------|-------------|
| **CONCATENATE** | `=CONCATENATE(text1, [text2], ...)` | Joins text (older version). |
| **TEXTJOIN** | `=TEXTJOIN(delimiter, ignore_empty, text1, [text2], ...)` | Joins text with a delimiter. |
| **LEFT** | `=LEFT(text, [num_chars])` | Extracts text from the left. |
| **RIGHT** | `=RIGHT(text, [num_chars])` | Extracts text from the right. |
| **MID** | `=MID(text, start_num, num_chars)` | Extracts text from the middle. |
| **TRIM** | `=TRIM(text)` | Removes extra spaces. |

---

## **5. Date & Time Functions**
| Function | Syntax | Description |
|----------|--------|-------------|
| **TODAY** | `=TODAY()` | Returns current date. |
| **NOW** | `=NOW()` | Returns current date & time. |
| **DATEDIF** | `=DATEDIF(start_date, end_date, "unit")` | Calculates date difference. |
| **DATE** | `=DATE(year, month, day)` | Creates a date from values. |

---

## **6. Financial Functions**
| Function | Syntax | Description |
|----------|--------|-------------|
| **PMT** | `=PMT(rate, nper, pv, [fv], [type])` | Calculates loan payments. |
| **FV** | `=FV(rate, nper, pmt, [pv], [type])` | Future value of an investment. |

---

## **7. Dynamic Array Functions (Excel 365)**
| Function | Syntax | Description |
|----------|--------|-------------|
| **FILTER** | `=FILTER(array, include, [if_empty])` | Filters data dynamically. |
| **UNIQUE** | `=UNIQUE(array, [by_col], [exactly_once])` | Extracts unique values. |
| **SORT** | `=SORT(array, [sort_index], [sort_order], [by_col])` | Sorts a range. |
